#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing Passwords"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/credentials.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "To change a user's password, type in a new one.  A `Reset Password` button will show up that you click after you've typed everything in.\n"
"If the `Temporary` switch is on, this new password can only be used once and the user will be asked to change their password after they have\n"
"logged in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/credentials.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternatively, if you have <<_email, email>> set up, you can send an email to the user that asks\n"
"them to reset their password.  Choose `Update Password` from the `Reset Actions` list box and click `Send Email`. You can optionally\n"
"set the validity of the e-mail link which defaults to the one preset in `Tokens` tab in the realm settings.\n"
"The sent email contains a link that will bring the user to the update password screen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/credentials.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing OTPs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/credentials.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot configure One-Time Passwords for a specific user within the Admin Console.  This is the responsibility of the user.\n"
"If the user has lost their OTP generator all you can do is disable OTP for them on the `Credentials` tab.\n"
"If OTP is optional in your realm, the user will have to go to the User Account Management service to re-configure a new\n"
"OTP generator. If OTP is required, then the user will be asked to re-configure a new OTP generator when they log in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/credentials.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Like passwords, you can alternatively send an email to the user that will ask them to reset their OTP generator.  Choose\n"
"`Configure OTP` in the `Reset Actions` list box and click the `Send Email` button.  The sent email\n"
"contains a link that will bring the user to the OTP setup screen.\n"
msgstr ""

